  ('en', 'Escalade', 'In climbing, which system constitutes an anchor point in the rock ?', 'Closing', 'Grigri', 'Carabiner', 'Relay', '1', 'This anchor can serve as a protection point in a length or progression, or serve as a relay.', ''),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What equipment grips the climber\'s pelvis like a harness ?', 'Baudrier', 'Strap ring', 'Closing', 'Crash pad', '1', 'The harness is widely used in the practice of various sports such as climbing, mountaineering, canyoning and speleology.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climbing harness'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What white powder is used to avoid sweating climbing hands ?', 'Magnets', 'Flour', 'Talc', 'Ice sugar', '1', 'The carbonate of magnesium may contain a small proportion of silica which, inhaled, can have adverse effects on the lungs.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnesium_carbonate'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What type of shoes is generally used for climbing ?', 'Slipper', 'Boot', 'Slipper', 'Basketball', '1', 'In order to improve the grip of the foot by friction on a wall of climbing or a rock, the slipper is covered with a layer of rubber.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climbing_shoe'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'Which of these quotes is considered the highest for an experienced climber ?', '9a', '7c +', '1a', 'e7', '1', 'The difficulty is estimated for an ascent to the head, without the help of belay points and without resting on the rope.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grade_(climbing)'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What does « lover a rope » mean in climber terminology ?', 'To wind up', 'Hang', 'Detach', 'Unlock', '2', 'The use is said to be simple when the sportsman is insured by a single strand of rope and double by two independent strands.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynamic_rope'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What is the nationality of the Petzl brand, among others known for its headlamps ?', 'French', 'American', 'English', 'Austrian', '2', 'The brand Petzl offers equipment for mountaineering, climbing, speleology, via ferrata, canyoning and trail running.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petzl'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What knot well known to climbers makes it possible to cow in complete safety ?', 'Capstan', 'Chair', 'Butterfly', 'Fisherman', '2', 'The capstan knot is tied to the lifeline in a carabiner: the rope is then locked in both directions.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clove_hitch'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What part of the climbing wall is called the d-verse ?', 'Leaning', 'Right', 'Vertical', 'On the edge', '2', 'In 1983, François Savigny invented the removable climbing catches, first in sandstone and then in resin concrete.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climbing_wall'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'In what safety system can we pass a rope when climbing ?', 'Carabiner', 'Tampon', 'Piolet', 'Crash pad', '2', 'The use of the climbing carabiner was in fact a logical consequence of the use of pitons invented by Hans Fiechtl.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carabiner'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What is the other name sometimes given by rosin climbers ?', 'Pof', 'Jumar', 'Loin', 'Clip', '2', 'The pof or rosin is a resin that the musicians put on the hair of the bows. In climbing, the pof waterproofs and sticks.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rosin'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'In rock climbing, what other term is used to caraband ?', 'Clipper', 'Broach', 'Corder', 'Flasher', '2', 'Appearing in the 1980s, sports climbing is one of the most modern climbing types and also the safest practice.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glossary_of_climbing_terms'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What rules do you have to follow to keep your balance in climbing ?', 'Three points', 'Full hand', 'Internal square', 'Zero time', '2', 'It consists of constantly maintaining at least three points of support during the progression (two feet one hand or two hands one foot).', ''),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'In which book are the routes of escalation and their difficulty recounted ?', 'Topo-guide', 'Lunule', 'Prussik', 'Serap', '2', 'Topos can also offer information on history, local dining options, bars and accommodations.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climbing guidebook'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'In climbing, what does one give when one assures one\'s partner in mind ?', 'Slack', 'Resistance', 'A basket', 'A harness', '2', 'The insurer can thus block his removal in case the climber falls on a brake or a self-locking device.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climbing'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What material is needed in addition to the pitches to climb a cliff ?', 'Cow', 'Beier', 'Sheep', 'Chamois', '3', 'The cow or loin consists of a ring of strap and its carabiner and a piece of dynamic rope.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climbing'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'Which high-level climber is commonly referred to as the French Spiderman ?', 'Alain Robert', 'Patrick Edlinger', 'Charles Albert', 'Jeff Mercier', '3', 'Alain Robert specializes in rock climbing solo and then in building climbing, also in solo solo.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alain_Robert'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What knot do you need to perform after a chair knot ?', 'Stop node', 'Lorenzi\'s knight', 'Butterfly nut', 'Heart Nut', '3', 'Unlike the eight knot, which can be difficult to loosen after a fall, the chair knot is easy to loosen.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bowline'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What is the best way to make a pathway ?', 'Quick link', 'Cordelette', 'Carabiner', 'Dégain', '3', 'For three generations, Péguet is the manufacturer of the Quick Link for any permanent or semi-permanent connection.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climbing'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'Which climber participated in 2004 in an advertisement for Grany ceramics ?', 'Patrick Edlinger', 'Laurent Jacob', 'Daniel Du Lac', 'Roman Manual', '3', 'Reputed for his climbs in full solo, Patrick Edlinger is one of the great pioneers of free climbing high level.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patrick_Edlinger'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What is the name of the most famous route made by Fred Rouhling ?', 'Akira', 'Silence', 'Dreamtime', 'Hubble', '3', 'In 1995, Fred Rouhling opened Akira and offered the untimely rating of 9b, which will lead to many climbers\' reactions.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fred_Rouhling'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'Which node should be used for rappelling with an oval carabiner ?', 'Half capstan', 'Nose in eight', 'Chair bow', 'Flat knot', '3', 'This node can be used to ensure a climbing climber or the replacement of a chute when one has lost it.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Munter_hitch'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'In which climbing mode are we climbing an untested track ?', 'In sight', 'Flash', 'Trad', 'Urban', '3', 'This climbing mode for savvy climbers is considered more difficult than climbing up or climbing after work.', ''),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'Since 1875, how was climbing formerly called ?', 'Rock climbing', 'Vairon', 'Valdrague', 'Vantance', '3', 'This name comes from several rocky corridors of Mount Salève, near Geneva where, from 1862, climbers found themselves friendly.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climbing'),
  ('en', 'Escalade', 'What European standard governs artificial climbing structures ?', 'EN 12572', 'RG 165', 'BD 432', 'KC 8855', '3', 'France has developed a second standard, experimentally in 2005: the standard XP P 90-312.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climbing_wall'),
  ('de', 'Escalade', 'Wie viel muss man vorgeben, klettern zu können ?', 'Eins', 'Zwei', 'Drei', 'Vier', '1', 'Das Sportklettern wird auf voll ausgestatteten Strecken durchgeführt, auf denen zuvor Ankerpunkte eingerichtet wurden.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Klettern'),
  ('de', 'Escalade', 'Welchen wichtigen Knoten müssen wir wissen, wie man Klettern macht ?', 'Nase in acht', 'Stuhlbogen', 'Flacher Knoten', 'Fliege', '1', 'Der Knoten in Acht ist relativ einfach zu demontieren, beschädigt das Seil nicht zu sehr und bildet einen Knoten, der größer ist als der einfache Knoten.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endacht'),
  ('de', 'Escalade', 'Welche Downhill-Technik wird an einem Seil mit Bremssystem trainiert ?', 'Erinnerung', 'Tiroler', 'Versichern', 'Behinderung', '1', 'Die Erfindung der Abseiltechnik im Jahre 1876 wurde Jean Charlet-Straton, einem Chamonix-Führer, zugeschrieben.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abseilen'),
  ('de', 'Escalade', 'Was muss ich tun, wenn ich beschließe, nur Stecker mit der gleichen Farbe an einer Wand zu verwenden ?', 'Weg', 'Pfad', 'Kurs', 'Verfolgt', '1', 'Ein Kletterpfad ist ein Pfad, durch den ein Kletterer die Spitze eines Berges oder eines Felsens erreicht.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kletterroute'),
  ('de', 'Escalade', 'Welches dieser Zitate bedeutet ein offizielles Schwierigkeitsniveau beim Klettern ?', '7C', '2-4', 'C2', 'B +', '1', 'Der Kletterer, der den ersten Anstieg einer Spur erreicht, ist normalerweise derjenige, der die ersten Chancen der Spur angibt.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Schwierigkeitsskala_(Klettern)'),
  ('de', 'Escalade', 'Welches System stellt beim Klettern einen Ankerpunkt im Felsen dar ?', 'Schließen', 'Grigri', 'Karabiner', 'Relais', '1', 'Dieser Anker kann als Schutzpunkt in einer Länge oder Progression dienen oder als Relais dienen.', ''),
  ('de', 'Escalade', 'Mit welcher Ausrüstung greift das Becken des Bergsteigers wie ein Gurtzeug ?', 'Baudrier', 'Riemenring', 'Schließen', 'Sturzpad', '1', 'Das Geschirr wird häufig in der Ausübung verschiedener Sportarten wie Klettern, Bergsteigen, Canyoning und Höhlenforschung eingesetzt.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Klettergurt'),
  ('de', 'Escalade', 'Welches weiße Pulver wird verwendet, um das Klettern an den Händen zu vermeiden ?', 'Magnete', 'Mehl', 'Talk', 'Eiszucker', '1', 'Das Carbonat von Magnesium kann einen geringen Anteil an Siliciumdioxid enthalten, der sich beim Einatmen nachteilig auf die Lunge auswirken kann.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnesiumcarbonat'),
  ('de', 'Escalade', 'Welche Schuhe werden im Allgemeinen zum Klettern verwendet ?', 'Slipper', 'Boot', 'Slipper', 'Basketball', '1', 'Um den Halt des Fußes durch Reibung an einer Kletterwand oder einem Felsen zu verbessern, ist der Slipper mit einer Gummischicht bedeckt.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kletterschuh'),
  ('de', 'Escalade', 'Welches dieser Zitate gilt für einen erfahrenen Bergsteiger als das höchste ?', '9a', '7c +', '1a', 'e7', '1', 'Die Schwierigkeit wird für einen Aufstieg zum Kopf geschätzt, ohne Hilfe von Sicherungspunkten und ohne auf dem Seil zu ruhen.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Schwierigkeitsskala_(Klettern)'),
  ('de', 'Escalade', 'Was bedeutet « ein Seil » in der Kletterer-Terminologie ?', 'Aufziehen', 'Hängen', 'Trennen Sie', 'Entsperren', '2', 'Die Verwendung gilt als einfach, wenn der Sportler durch einen einzelnen Seilstrang und zwei durch zwei unabhängige Stränge versichert ist.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kletterseil'),
